row.cell:
1870-1890 US population doubles;

Rapid growth in newspapers: daily newspapers quadruple; numbers sold increased sixfold; circulation totals for all daily publications rose from 2.6 in 1870 to 15 million in 1900

weekly newspapers tripled from 4,000 to 12,000

1877 Sister Bertha Wilkinson born;

Wilkinsons buy home in Winsor Park on Bond Ave, to later be called the “House-home;”

Elia meets Robert Burns Peattie who then worked for the Western News Company

1893 Peattie reads three papers at the Exposition;

Helps organize the Omaha Woman’s Club;

Wilkinsons move to South Haven, MI and the “House-home” is divided into rental apartments
